works.description: My entire website of content including business name, logo, all text content, images, photo, graphics, SEO, metadata over an 8+ year timeframe has been stolen and someone else purchased the domain http://johimadesigns.ca and stole my work to put on it. I know that someone else can purchase the domain as I gave it up. However, they are 100% infringing upon copyright with the theft of all of my work, my entire website ... even my own phone number and contact information remains on the site. I can prove all of this, as I designed the site, and have all Dreamweaver, Illustrator and Photoshop files here. I wrote all the metadata for search engine optimization, and all of the text content on the site.
